	<!-- ========================================
	     DEVELOPER NOTES
	     ======================================== -->

	<!--
	SETUP INSTRUCTIONS:

	1. NFC Tag Reading:
	   - Must request capability in Apple Developer Portal
	   - Fill out NFC usage questionnaire
	   - May take 1-2 business days for approval
	   - Required for production builds

	2. Apple Pay Merchant ID:
	   - Create merchant ID in Apple Developer Portal
	   - Navigate to: Certificates, IDs & Profiles → Identifiers → Merchant IDs
	   - Click + to create new merchant ID
	   - Format: merchant.com.ea-solutions.wiesbaden-after-dark
	   - Create payment processing certificate
	   - Configure merchant ID in Stripe dashboard

	3. Wallet Pass Type ID:
	   - Create pass type ID in Apple Developer Portal
	   - Navigate to: Certificates, IDs & Profiles → Identifiers → Pass Type IDs
	   - Click + to create new pass type ID
	   - Format: pass.com.ea-solutions.wiesbaden-after-dark
	   - Create pass signing certificate
	   - Download certificate and add to Keychain

	4. Push Notifications:
	   - Change aps-environment to 'production' for App Store builds
	   - Keep as 'development' for TestFlight and local testing
	   - Configure APNs key or certificate in developer portal
	   - Register device tokens in your backend

	5. Bundle Identifier:
	   - Must match the bundle ID in your Xcode project
	   - Format: com.ea-solutions.WiesbadenAfterDark
	   - Must match merchant ID and pass type ID prefixes

	6. Team ID:
	   - Required for some entitlements (App Groups, iCloud)
	   - Found in Apple Developer Portal under Membership
	   - Format: XXXXXXXXXX (10 characters)

	IMPORTANT FOR APP STORE SUBMISSION:
	- All merchant IDs and pass type IDs must be registered in Apple Developer Portal
	- NFC capability must be approved before submission
	- Push notification capability must be enabled
	- Xcode project must have "Capabilities" tab properly configured
	- All entitlements must match your provisioning profile

	TESTING NOTES:
	- NFC will NOT work in Simulator (requires physical device)
	- Apple Pay works in Simulator for testing (uses test cards)
	- Wallet passes can be tested in Simulator
	- Push notifications require physical device or Simulator with APNs
	-->

